Welcome to Ancient Oaks
Welcome to our vibrant 55+ community, nestled on 40 scenic acres along the north side of beautiful Lake Okeechobee, and home to 686 units. More than just a place to live, our park is brought to life by residents who fill it with camaraderie, laughter, games, and engaging activities.
We encourage residents to share this special place with visiting friends and family, offering them a glimpse of the warmth, fun, and hospitality that define our community. Whether you're a full-time resident or a seasonal visitor, you'll find this community to be a welcoming and valuable resource—no matter where you call home.
Our Board of Directors consists of five elected volunteers who reside within the park. Supporting them is our dedicated on-site park manager, who helps maintain the park and ensures it remains a safe, clean, and enjoyable environment for all. Residents pay quarterly dues, which cover essential services including water and sewer plants, basic cable, lawn care, trash pickup, and upkeep of all common areas.
A lively, volunteer-run Social Committee organizes a wide range of events and entertainment at the clubhouse and throughout the grounds—ensuring there’s always something fun for everyone.
We also welcome prospective residents and guests to explore our community online. This website features current listings of properties for sale or rent. All prospective renters and buyers should contact the property owners directly. If you are interested in purchasing in our community, please contact our office to begin the New Buyer Process.
So come on down, soak up the sun, and discover why so many love to call this place home.

Social Events
rpmservices
2023-11-27T19:49:28+00:00
STILL STANDING TOUR
Elton John Tribute Concert
Ladies Style Show
Every year the Social Activities Committee holds a  Ladies Style Show which is held in the Clubhouse.  There is always over 200 in attendance to view and shop for jewelry, tops, pants, purses, dresses and other clothing accessories. Several outfits are modeled by some of our very own ladies. (See pictures below).  A light lunch is also served.
NEW YEARS EVE PARTY
CHRISTMAS PARTY
FLEETWOOD MAX
The Band, Fleetwood Max performed a tribute to the 1970’s  pop group “Fleetwood Mac”.  In this writers opinion, this was the best concert, in Ancient Oaks, in my 9 years here.  Fleetwood Max had the audience stomping their feet, clapping their hands, dancing and singing along, too many of our favorite songs that we loved years ago.  If you missed this concert and you’re a Fleetwood Mac fan, you goofed!
The gal that performed the Stevie Nicks part was fabulous.  She sounded and acted exactly like the original Stevie Nicks. Below are a few pictures from this performance.
ART AND ARTISAN SHOW
As you can tell by the attached photos, there are many talented people in our park.  Sewing, painting, furniture making, jewelry making, etc. were on display.  Some were available to purchase and others were simply for viewing.
The event is greatly attended and was is used as a fund raiser for the Social Activities Committee.  A bake sale was used to raise additional funds for future park enhancements.  Thanks to the many that volunteered there time and baking skills to donate bake goods.
JEFF GORDON CONTRY LEGIONS
Watching this performance was a real treat.  What a great performance by Jeff Gordon.  Jeff having spent 18 years performing in Branson, Mo. brought a truly professional act to Ancient Oaks.  Jeff performed tributes to Garth Brooks, George Straight, Johnny Cash, Merle Haggard, Willie Nelson, Waylon Jennings, Conway Twitty, etc. for 2 hours and 45 minutes.  The crowd was whistling, yelling and dancing to songs and artists from past decades.
Below are a few pictures from this event:
US Bee Gee’s Tribute Band
THE SKY FAMILY BLAZING FIDDLES
The Sky Family direct from Prince Edward Island, Canada featured Celtic music and humor along with a Gospel Revival performance.
Below are a few pictures from that performance:
